Detailed Description

Represents one of the program_parameters that define the program usage.

Define Documentation

void geoxml_program_parameter_set_keyword ( GeoXmlProgramParameter *  program_parameter,
const gchar *  keyword 
)

Set program_parameter keyword to keyword.

The keyword is the identifier of the program_parameter in program. For example, if keyword is 'infile' and value is 'data.su' a command line with 'infile=data.su' will be generated to run the program. If program_parameter is a flag, you should set keyword to the string that activates it on the program (e.g. style=normal in SU ximage).

If program_parameter is NULL nothing is done.

See also:
geoxml_program_parameter_get_keyword

GString* geoxml_program_parameter_get_string_value ( GeoXmlProgramParameter *  program_parameter,
gboolean  default_value 
)

Otherwise, return the same as geoxml_program_parameter_get_first_value. The GString pointer should be freed by you.
